parameters: Isn't this the same mirror that was in class?
CaveOpening_Cutscene
Racing through the newly found opening, hearing the
cave starting to crumble beneath your feet, you see an
opening ahead.
BlankMountainSideView_Cutscene
Finally making it to the top of the cave opening and
you managed to escape the cave collapsing.
You're brought into the early morning light.
You all see your breath blooming before you and turning
around. The sky above is full of warm hues and straight
ahead beyond the city of Hazelfair is Darkmore Lake...
You see mist floating off the ever still water and
there's a chill in the air. Taking a moment to catch
your breath, you sit down and take in the view.
Despite being coated in dirt and grime, you survived.
There is a slight glint in the distance and the sun is
starting to rise.
To your left, you see a large creature.
Laphicet_Cutscene
On the cliff side of the mountain below the Apexium, an
orange creature starts to emerge from a cliffside cave.
Even though you're far away, the creature is large and
coming more into view, you recognize it's a dragon,
specifically,
Laphicet, the Topaz Dragon of the Fall Court.
As the sun starts to shine a beam of light across the
treetops, Laphicet extends his wings to they're full
wingspan and stretches, he releases a puff of his
glowing fumes that reflect against the sun's light. He
shakes his head and looks across the Court.
It's breathtaking.
Before he returns back to his cave, turning and
swishing is tail like a cat then disappearing into the
mountain again, he leaves you all to walk back in the
early crisp morning air,
For your new day of classes.
And that's where we will end today's session.
